profile_positions.description:
Manage a team of 2 Account Payable Specialist
Creation and implementation and management of the P2P Purchase-to-payment) process within the SSC and setting up of the tools necessary to achieve this effectively and accurately and in a timely fashion. 
Handle calls/emails from vendors and business units on items such as requests for invoice status, providing documentation, and working account reconciliations with our vendors. 
Tasked with backup responsibility for all functional positions in the Accounts Payable EU group, including but not limited to scanning, invoice PO and FI posting, journal entries, logistics invoices, recurring entries, Metrics reporting, travel management applications and credit card systems administration; 
Detect and coordinate resolution with appropriate personnel; 
Ascertain that invoice approvals are in accordance with the company’s Delegation of Authority; 
Assist manager with responses to internal audit questions and reviews. 
Supports the external quarterly reviews, annual audits and SOX 404 internal control audits, and assists in providing support for related accounts payable request; 
Develop, improve and document all processes within the Accounts Payable department
